  "name": "details: a check-in with no check-out re-prompts — the B7 'TBC' path is deliberately gone (B8/F16)",
  "comment": "Deliberate revision of B7 behaviour, not a regression. B7 accepted a check-in-only booking and rendered the check-out as 'TBC'. Once a booking holds a room, a booking with no check-out holds that room against a range the overlap check cannot see — it would block nothing and could never be collided with, quietly re-opening the double-booking B8 exists to close. The greeting has always said 'Send all three'; this makes the code agree with the copy. Cost: a two-line message re-prompts instead of creating a TBC booking.",
